What are you doing?

11:42.269 --> 11:44.802
You should be out there
pounding the pavement.

11:44.871 --> 11:47.538
I tried putt's farm,
kirkland's garage, nothing!

11:47.607 --> 11:49.540
I got all the way down
to the flemings,

11:49.576 --> 11:50.942
But they already bought
theirs off suzanne.

11:50.944 --> 11:52.076
She's got the whole road
limbed out!

11:52.079 --> 11:53.477
Well, get back out there!

11:53.513 --> 11:55.814
No!

11:55.949 --> 11:57.648
I'm, uh, here
for the, um, package.

11:57.684 --> 11:58.950
Oh, yeah, yeah.

11:59.085 --> 12:01.853
Thank you.

12:01.855 --> 12:02.787
There you go.
Whoa--

12:02.789 --> 12:04.889
What're you up to?

12:04.958 --> 12:06.190
Beer?

12:06.226 --> 12:08.058
Pop: Good, thank you.

12:08.095 --> 12:11.362
Look, I know a guy
who works on a beer truck.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.965
A few cases got redirected...

12:14.100 --> 12:16.167
Mary: Stolen!
Pop: Diverted.

12:16.302 --> 12:20.505
And I'm just out there to help
him get it out into the world.

12:20.640 --> 12:22.240
Catch and release.

12:22.309 --> 12:24.842
You bloody bootlegger!
This is illegal.

12:24.911 --> 12:26.644
Plus, those hard-working boys
down at the brewery

12:26.780 --> 12:28.379
Are trying to save their jobs,
ya frigger!

12:28.381 --> 12:29.981
Look, calm down, will you?

12:30.050 --> 12:31.515
It's not gonna happen again.

12:31.551 --> 12:34.218
[knock at door]

12:34.287 --> 12:36.020
Ah.

12:36.022 --> 12:37.388
Loyola.

12:37.390 --> 12:39.456
You change your mind
about that citrus soap?

12:39.493 --> 12:41.926
Uh, no, mary.
I'm here for pat.

12:41.962 --> 12:43.461
Pat, do you have that package?

12:43.596 --> 12:44.862
I do indeed.

12:44.898 --> 12:46.797
He can't sell you any beer.

12:46.833 --> 12:49.466
But...

12:49.503 --> 12:52.203
He can give it to you
for free...

12:52.338 --> 12:54.539
With the purchase of
select avon products.

12:54.608 --> 12:56.574
Ignore her.

12:56.610 --> 12:58.543
Four dollars.

12:58.612 --> 13:00.511
Hey, either we do this together

13:00.514 --> 13:03.081
Or I drop you outside
that beer factory

13:03.083 --> 13:06.351
With a sign around your neck
saying "bootlegger."

13:06.486 --> 13:08.820
♪

13:08.955 --> 13:10.487
Pay the woman.

13:10.524 --> 13:12.757
Mary: Here.

13:12.826 --> 13:14.759
Hm!

13:14.761 --> 13:16.093
You gonna drink it or what?

13:16.129 --> 13:17.428
No, thank you.

13:17.564 --> 13:18.997
I'm more of a canadian beer guy.

13:19.132 --> 13:21.065
Ha!
Sook!

13:21.134 --> 13:23.034
Sook!

13:23.036 --> 13:27.171
Adult mark:<i> I knew</i>
<i> the dangers of drinking...</i>

13:27.174 --> 13:28.373
Mark: Oh, are you okay?

13:28.508 --> 13:30.775
Mike jr: Oh... I'm dying.
Bucket!

13:30.910 --> 13:32.377
[vomiting]

13:32.379 --> 13:35.513
Adult mark:<i> ...From</i>
<i> watching my brother.</i>

13:35.515 --> 13:37.915
Silver fox: Just like
I told my sister...

13:37.951 --> 13:39.650
You're a baby!

13:39.686 --> 13:40.952
Adult mark:<i> He had a point.</i>

13:41.087 --> 13:43.187
<i> There was no way</i>
<i> fox could say I was a baby</i>

13:43.190 --> 13:44.656
<i> If I was a drinking man.</i>

13:44.658 --> 13:49.594
<i> I mean, how bad could it be?</i>

13:49.663 --> 13:51.662
[exhales]

13:51.698 --> 13:53.764
Gentlemen, to your health!

13:56.336 --> 13:58.336
[laughter]

13:58.338 --> 14:00.104
Mark: Yuck, that stuff sucks!

14:00.240 --> 14:02.206
I mean,
that american stuff sucks.

14:02.242 --> 14:03.807
No booze in it!

14:03.844 --> 14:05.676
Silver fox: Nuh-uh.

14:05.745 --> 14:07.344
You don't leave here
without drinking.

14:07.380 --> 14:10.081
I don't want you to narc us out.

14:10.150 --> 14:11.316
Mark: Ha-ha, very funny.

14:11.451 --> 14:13.951
Brothers: Chug! Chug! Chug!
Chug! Chug! Chug!

14:13.987 --> 14:14.919
Chug--
[branch cracks]

14:15.054 --> 14:16.287
What was that?

14:16.422 --> 14:18.823
Sister rose: Come out, come out,
wherever you are!

14:18.892 --> 14:21.359
I can hear you!

14:21.361 --> 14:23.261
[in a whisper]
it's sister rose!

14:23.396 --> 14:24.728
Sister rose: I can't
see you, but god can!

14:24.764 --> 14:26.330
He sees you when
you're sleeping!

14:26.366 --> 14:27.665
He knows when you're awake!

14:27.667 --> 14:31.970
I followed a trail of
denuded chicken bones.

14:32.105 --> 14:36.207
Come on,
my little hansel and gretel!

14:36.209 --> 14:37.575
Silver fox: Don't... Move.

14:37.710 --> 14:38.943
Sister rose: You can't
hide forever!

14:39.078 --> 14:41.179
If I find you deserters,

14:41.181 --> 14:43.180
I'm gonna smack
the arse right off of ya!

14:43.216 --> 14:45.383
Adult mark:<i> I was terrified.</i>

14:45.452 --> 14:46.851
<i> It was a good thing</i>
<i> I wasn't sober.</i>

14:46.986 --> 14:48.052
Sister rose: Come out
and talk to me!

14:50.891 --> 14:52.523
Never
<i> having experienced booze,</i>

14:52.592 --> 14:55.860
<i> I took my anxiety</i>
<i> for being drunk.</i>

14:55.995 --> 14:59.230
Fee-fi-fo-fum!

14:59.299 --> 15:02.734
I smell the beer
of someone dumb!

15:02.736 --> 15:04.702
♪

15:04.738 --> 15:07.237
Adult mark:<i> They say humans</i>
<i> have two modes in crisis:</i>

15:07.274 --> 15:08.773
<i> Fight or flight.</i>

15:08.775 --> 15:10.207
<i> I had a third:</i>

15:10.243 --> 15:13.144
<i> Freeze.</i>

15:13.213 --> 15:15.546
<i> The fox brothers</i>
<i> ran smack into the nun,</i>

15:15.682 --> 15:18.650
<i>Just like moths to the flame.</i>

15:18.785 --> 15:21.619
<i>I thought I was old enough to</i>
<i>eat lunch off school grounds,</i>

15:21.754 --> 15:24.755
<i> But not even pop</i>
<i> was old enough for this!</i>

15:24.824 --> 15:27.091
So, you wanna watch some
wrestling with the old man?

15:27.160 --> 15:29.693
Ric flair is about to
take on angelo mosca!

15:29.729 --> 15:30.828
Yeah, sure.

15:30.897 --> 15:34.031
I guess.

15:34.167 --> 15:35.300
Dad?
[bell on tv rings]

15:35.435 --> 15:37.168
Yeah, kitten?

15:37.170 --> 15:38.369
It's nice when you don't drink.

15:38.504 --> 15:40.238
Jeez, b'y.

15:40.373 --> 15:41.906
So you really do think
I'm an alkie.

15:41.908 --> 15:43.241
No, no.

15:43.376 --> 15:44.775
I-I never meant it like that.

15:44.844 --> 15:47.712
I just meant...

15:47.847 --> 15:49.914
I want to spend more time here.

15:50.049 --> 15:52.082
[cheering on tv]

15:52.118 --> 15:54.551
It's your house too.

15:54.587 --> 15:56.720
Now, luh.
Ric flair.

15:56.756 --> 16:00.057
The stylin', profilin',
limousine ridin'--

16:00.126 --> 16:03.394
Both: Jet flying, kiss-stealing,
wheelin' and dealin'

16:03.396 --> 16:04.262
Son of a gun!

16:04.397 --> 16:05.496
Woo!

16:05.631 --> 16:08.599
Dad: [laughs]

16:08.635 --> 16:10.468
Here, give me a fry.
Give me a fry!

16:10.537 --> 16:12.603
Fox: It's my fries!
Stop it!

16:12.605 --> 16:14.839
No!

16:14.974 --> 16:17.208
♪

16:17.343 --> 16:19.677
Pop: Alright, that's two
blue star and a skin so soft.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.245
That comes to...

16:21.281 --> 16:23.147
Mary: Fourteen dollars.
Pop: Fourteen dollars.

16:23.216 --> 16:26.150
But, if you take a bar of
moonwind soap on a rope,

16:26.152 --> 16:29.420
We'll throw in two bottles
of blackhorse and call it 20.

16:29.456 --> 16:31.155
Alright, thank you.

16:31.191 --> 16:32.824
Mary: There you are.
Pop: Alright.

16:32.826 --> 16:34.225
[laughs]

16:34.294 --> 16:35.760
Pop: How're we doing?
Mary: Fifty-seven dollars.

16:35.895 --> 16:37.294
Voice: Pat?
You home?

16:37.296 --> 16:38.830
[in a whisper] what?
Officer butt!

16:38.832 --> 16:40.198
Quick, hide the stuff.

16:40.200 --> 16:43.234
Quick, throw that over.

16:43.236 --> 16:44.501
Mary: Oh!

16:44.537 --> 16:46.404
Officer butt,
what brings you here?

16:46.539 --> 16:48.940
I heard that there might be
some beer for sale here.

16:49.075 --> 16:50.508
Oh, that's ridiculous.

16:50.510 --> 16:52.976
Alright, look, we haven't
got time for this, piggie.

16:53.113 --> 16:54.645
Either arrest me or get lost.

16:54.681 --> 16:57.381
Your cop car out there,
it's scaring off our customers!

16:57.384 --> 16:58.982
Avon customers.

16:59.019 --> 17:00.317
I've been selling avon products.

17:00.353 --> 17:01.953
No law against that.

17:02.088 --> 17:04.455
Oh, well, that's too bad.

17:04.590 --> 17:07.991
I was looking for a few beer
to take up to my cabin.

17:08.028 --> 17:09.327
Can't drink that american piss.

17:09.462 --> 17:10.795
Oh!
[chuckles]

17:10.864 --> 17:14.132
Well, in that case,
you came to the right place.

17:15.668 --> 17:18.102
Four jockey club.

17:18.104 --> 17:20.571
And a bottle of sweet honesty
cologne for 30 bucks.

17:26.579 --> 17:28.479
Adult mark:<i> I was</i>
<i> as sober as a judge,</i>

17:28.614 --> 17:31.949
<i>But convinced that I was drunk.</i>

17:31.951 --> 17:34.218
<i> I was terrified that</i>
<i> the nun would call dad</i>

17:34.220 --> 17:39.624
<i> And I'd be sent to juvie</i>
<i>like mickey rooney in boystown!</i>

17:39.759 --> 17:41.692
What the hell
are you doing?

17:41.694 --> 17:42.726
Taking a walk.

17:42.762 --> 17:44.027
Hm.

17:44.064 --> 17:44.996
In the hallway?

17:45.131 --> 17:46.330
Sure.

17:46.332 --> 17:48.299
Sure.
Okay.

17:48.434 --> 17:50.968
So, walk.

17:51.104 --> 17:54.171
Mark: Ah...
Yeah.

17:54.240 --> 17:55.873
Hm.
School called.

17:56.008 --> 17:57.942
Mark: Well--
mike jr: Said you pipped off.

17:57.944 --> 17:59.777
Uh, I can explain.
I was just...

17:59.779 --> 18:01.646
I told them
you came home sick.

18:01.781 --> 18:02.813
So...?

18:02.816 --> 18:05.049
What--

18:05.184 --> 18:07.251
Is that pee?

18:07.253 --> 18:09.320
No, it's beer.

18:09.322 --> 18:10.988
No, it's pee.

18:10.990 --> 18:12.723
But it's not mine!
It's somebody else's!

18:12.725 --> 18:14.725
Oh, you smell like
the floor of a legion!

18:14.761 --> 18:18.329
How many did you have?

18:18.331 --> 18:20.631
One.

18:20.633 --> 18:22.099
Okay.

18:22.234 --> 18:23.468
Act normal.

18:23.603 --> 18:26.069
You're fine.

18:26.106 --> 18:28.673
♪

18:28.808 --> 18:30.207
Oh, dear god.

18:32.345 --> 18:35.746
I tallied up our take.

18:35.782 --> 18:37.414
I sold all my product
in one day.

18:37.416 --> 18:39.483
Ha!
A regular estee lauder.

18:39.486 --> 18:42.353
I had a pretty
interesting day myself.

18:42.355 --> 18:44.221
Thought I wouldn't
make it out of there alive.

18:44.257 --> 18:46.157
Like covering 'nam.

18:46.159 --> 18:47.825
"the battery
of bottle-breaking bottlers

18:47.827 --> 18:50.428
"left this broadcaster
black and blue."

18:50.430 --> 18:52.496
They're gonna be out
for a hell of a long time,

18:52.499 --> 18:53.831
Take my word on it.

18:53.833 --> 18:55.366
Mark: Father, mother, pop.

18:55.435 --> 18:57.168
How is everyone?

18:57.303 --> 18:58.903
Adult mark:<i> I took</i>
<i> my brother's advice.</i>

18:58.972 --> 19:01.438
<i> The least suspicious thing</i>
<i> to do was to act normally,</i>

19:01.474 --> 19:04.575
<i>Which, when you try to do it,</i>
<i> always seems suspicious.</i>

19:04.611 --> 19:05.977
Is that coffee?

19:05.979 --> 19:07.778
You drink tea.

19:07.847 --> 19:09.980
I felt like a cuppa' joe.

19:10.016 --> 19:11.582
What's that smell?

19:11.651 --> 19:13.116
It's...

19:13.153 --> 19:14.685
Uh...

19:14.721 --> 19:16.854
Uh...
The...

19:16.989 --> 19:18.623
Mike jr: Oh, it's mark.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.524
The little weirdo
got into your avon.

19:20.560 --> 19:21.659
Come on.

19:21.661 --> 19:22.793
Mark: What, uh...

19:22.862 --> 19:25.596
Mike jr: Up, up, up, up.

19:25.632 --> 19:28.666
[quietly] now, go wash up,
'cause you friggin' reek.

19:28.801 --> 19:30.368
Uh, apologies.

19:30.370 --> 19:31.802
Tv news:<i> Breaking news.</i>

19:31.871 --> 19:34.037
<i> Workers and the union</i>
<i> resolved the beer strike today</i>

19:34.073 --> 19:36.340
<i> After a 22-hour</i>
<i> bargaining session.</i>

19:36.376 --> 19:38.609
<i> The hangover is over.</i>

19:38.678 --> 19:40.611
I knew it wouldn't last.

19:40.647 --> 19:41.945
No more american beer.

19:41.981 --> 19:44.081
You must be happy, pop.

19:44.150 --> 19:45.349
Mark: Good.

19:45.385 --> 19:47.217
That american beer is awful.

19:47.219 --> 19:48.653
Mary: Hm?

19:48.655 --> 19:49.820
So I hear.

19:49.822 --> 19:51.522
Goodnight.

19:51.524 --> 19:54.025
♪

19:54.027 --> 19:56.227
Tv news:<i> The strike resolution</i>
<i> means that newfoundlanders</i>

19:56.229 --> 19:58.495
<i> Can once again</i>
<i> buy canadian beer.</i>

19:58.531 --> 20:01.164
<i> Sales of beer had dropped</i>
<i> 50% in the capital city,</i>

20:01.201 --> 20:02.366
<i> With some stores...</i>

20:02.435 --> 20:04.435
Okay, I gotta
pop out for a minute.

20:04.437 --> 20:05.436
Dad?

20:05.571 --> 20:08.171
Dad: I'll be right back.

20:08.208 --> 20:10.441
Adult mark:<i> Fox had been</i>
<i> the only person in town</i>

20:10.443 --> 20:12.009
<i> Happy for the beer strike.</i>

20:12.078 --> 20:14.711
<i> Her father was the rare man</i>
<i> who promised more sober</i>

20:14.747 --> 20:18.182
<i> Than he did drunk.</i>

20:18.251 --> 20:22.520
<i>Fox knew the reality of beer.</i>

20:22.655 --> 20:24.922
<i> I had been seduced</i>
<i> by the mystery of it.</i>

20:25.057 --> 20:28.058
<i> But, like fox, I, too,</i>
<i> had become a teetotaller.</i>

20:28.094 --> 20:31.929
[knock at door]

20:32.064 --> 20:33.698
Are you alive?

20:33.700 --> 20:35.633
The room's spinning.

20:35.635 --> 20:38.469
Here.

20:38.604 --> 20:41.472
Come on, take it.

20:41.607 --> 20:42.773
Ugh, I don't want beer!

20:42.908 --> 20:45.209
It's not beer,
it's flat ginger ale.

20:45.278 --> 20:49.680
Pretty much the same stuff you
were drinking earlier, though.

20:49.815 --> 20:52.483
Mike jr: I remember
my first beer.

20:52.552 --> 20:53.951
How old were you?

20:53.953 --> 20:55.352
Sixteen.

20:55.488 --> 20:57.021
Wait, I had my
first beer before you did?

20:57.156 --> 21:00.190
Ha-ha, shut up!

21:00.260 --> 21:03.894
And hey, saying yes to things
doesn't make you tough.

21:03.930 --> 21:06.029
Saying no does.

21:06.065 --> 21:09.500
Don't let people
push you into things.

21:09.569 --> 21:11.369
Adult mark:<i> My brother</i>
<i> was right.</i>

21:11.504 --> 21:15.106
<i>Why worry about peer pressure</i>
<i> when I barely had any peers?</i>

21:15.108 --> 21:18.775
<i>I would be on my own personal</i>
<i> beer strike for a long time.</i>

21:18.811 --> 21:21.779
[gagging]

21:21.781 --> 21:23.180
[vomiting]

21:23.182 --> 21:26.384
♪

21:26.519 --> 21:30.120
♪

21:30.189 --> 21:34.258
♪

21:34.393 --> 21:38.329
♪

21:38.331 --> 21:42.666
♪

21:42.669 --> 21:46.504
♪

21:46.506 --> 21:50.074
♪
